    <div rend="parallel">
      <lg xml:id="TolE0268">
<l>pūve ṉorupeya rāyiyal piṉṟē</l>
<l>yāvayiṉ valleḻuttu mikutalu murittē</l>
      </lg>
      <lg xml:lang="en">
<l>That change does not take place with the one noun <foreign xml:lang="ta">pū</foreign> ' flower ' ;</l>
<l>in that place, the stop may be inserted.<note place="foot">i.e., <foreign xml:lang="ta">pū + koṭi &gt; pūkkoṭi</foreign> and not <foreign xml:lang="ta">*pūukkoṭi.</foreign> Though the aphorism does not mention a nasal insertion, Iḷam. also quotes <foreign xml:lang="ta">
          pūṅkoṭi</foreign> etc. as a possibility (in analogy with <foreign xml:lang="ta">oṭuṅkōṭu</foreign> etc.? Cf. 244 and 263).</note></l>
     </lg>
    </div>
  </body>
